<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-174-602  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 174 602.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  March 28 1989 v3 n13 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple slates multimedia videodiscs. (Visual Almanac andInteractive Nova)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Guglielmo, Connie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   Visual Almanac (Information retrieval system)Interactive Nova (information retrieval system) (productintroduction)Hypercard (Data base management system) (product development).andO;Topic:     Video SystemsInteractive VideoEducational SoftwareData BasesMicrocomputersProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Apple slates multimedia videodiscsandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- Apple plans to publish two interactive multimediaproducts in the next few months as part of its emerging campaign formultimedia technology on the Macintosh.andM;The Visual Almanac and Interactive Nova videodisks are driven by HyperCard,said Sueann Ambron, co-director of Apple's Multimedia Lab in San Francisco.andM;Visual Almanac, created by designers at the lab, is a compilation ofinformation and activities designed as a resource for teachers.andP;  It containstext, graphics, sound and video images on a variety of subjects from physicsto history.andM;Apple also funded Interactive Nova, a presentation developed by Boston-basedWGBH Educational Foundation, creator of the Nova science series aired on thePublic Broadcasting System.andP;  Under development for three years, the two-discpresentation is based on a Nova program about animal migration called&quot;Mystery of Animal Pathfinders,&quot; said Ted Sicker, project director.andM;One disc contains the complete &quot;Animal Pathfinders&quot; show, along with stillimages and other video footage shot for the presentation.andP;  Another disccontains a stack of more than 600 cards with information on animals, as wellas three interactive activities and a resource section containing a glossary,references and maps, Sicker said.andM;Both Visual Almanac and Interactive Nova contain tools that allow users toput together reports or videos using any information included in thepresentations.andM;Apple also is putting together a list of about 100 multimedia consultantsnationwide with the resources to help organizations create multimediapresentations.andO;</TEXT></DOC>